# Live Telemetry System - User Guide

## 🎯 Overview
Your system now uses **real live data** stored in **SQL Server** instead of random seeded data. The frontend displays actual telemetry data from the database.

---

## 📊 System Architecture

```
IoT Simulator (PowerShell/ConsolePublisher)
	↓ HTTP POST
API Backend (ASP.NET Core) - http://localhost:5297
	↓ Store
SQL Server Database (TelemetryDb)
	↑ Query
Frontend (Angular) - http://localhost:4200
```

---

## 🚀 Quick Start

### 1. Start the Backend API
```powershell
cd MQTTR1
dotnet run
```
Backend will run on: `http://localhost:5297`

### 2. Start the Frontend
```powershell
cd mqttr-frontend
npm start
```
Frontend will run on: `http://localhost:4200`

### 3. Send Live Telemetry Data

**Option A: One-time batch (300 readings - historical data with 2-minute intervals)**
```powershell
.\send-live-data.ps1
```
*Generates 100 readings per device with 2-minute intervals (covers ~3.3 hours of historical data)*

**Option B: Continuous simulation (sends data every 2 minutes)**
```powershell
.\continuous-simulator.ps1
```
Press `Ctrl+C` to stop

*Sends telemetry readings every 2 minutes for real-time data collection*

**Option C: Use ConsolePublisher (Interactive)**
```powershell
cd ConsolePublisher
dotnet run -- http://localhost:5297/api
```
Then select option 3 to simulate continuous IoT device

